Brian
ACM stands for the Association for Computing Machinery.  The are a global organization that researches technology and develops computing standards.  We have a chapter here at NAU.  But basically it is just a club where we talk about doing fun stuff like LAN parties and we have an interesting speaker every week and watch an awesome movie at the end.
That sounds a lot like PRSSA. Where all we do is fundraising to go conferences get nifty t-shirts and have guest spearkers. but it sounds like a fun club.

Hey,
You seemed pretty cool about the potentially pending break-up.  When I said "We should talk" in my text I just wanted to make sure you're OK.  I know we joke around a lot, but a 2 and a half year relationship sounds pretty serious.  I think you deserve a great guy that meets your every want and need.  So I encourage you to really evaluate your relationship, maybe even list out all the Pros and Cons, just to be sure that you aren't making a mistake.  I am sure you won't be single for very long, you are quite a catch!  I am here to talk to if you need anything.
